==English==

===Noun===
'''top-of-mind awareness'''  

# (Advertising) the percentage of respondents who, without prompting, name a specific brand or product ''first'' when asked to list all the ads they recall seeing in a general product category over the past 30 days, in advertising research.
#:''Companies that are well known, advertise heavily, and have attention-getting ads tend to receive the highest '''top-of-mind awareness''' scores in [[continuous advertising tracking|ad tracking]] studies.''

